# Defining a Protocol

We define a Protocol using the `protocol` keyword.

```swift
protocol Drivable {
    // A required property (must be gettable and settable)
    var topSpeed: Int { get set }

    // A required method (Notice there are NO curly braces!)
    func startEngine()
}
```
Here, we created the `Drivable` rulebook. Notice there's no actual code inside the method! We only wrote the *signature* of the function.
